Confirmed the root cause by adding wait in TM 
```
while (task.getExecutionState() == ExecutionState.RUNNING) {
    try {
        Thread.sleep(1000);
    } catch (InterruptedException e) {
        throw new RuntimeException(e);
    }
}
```
to `TaskExecutor.sendOperatorEventToTask` after [this](https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/2db7996c95fd02eafc59c0dfd08ad9f726170266/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/taskexecutor/TaskExecutor.java#L1430) line 
(not included in the commit).

Explanation:
```
// Fail SideOutputITCase.testWatermarkForwarding.
// The test source is about to finish (it emits just one record before END_OF_INPUT),
// and any attempt to deliver an event to a FINISHED task fails the job.
// However, usually it's delivered while the task is still RUNNING; or it finishes before
// the RPC starts - so the executor on JM is shut down before delivery attempt.
// Here, we deliberately wait for the task to FINISH to fail the test:
```

The fix is to not finish the source task until the coordinator sends the `NoMoreSplitsEvent` event.
